definitions.definition: ( transitive and intransitive ) To be a member of a vessel's crew
examples: We crewed together on a fishing boat last year.
The ship was crewed by fifty sailors.

definitions.definition: To be a member of a work or production crew
examples: The film was crewed and directed by students.

definitions.definition: To supply workers or sailors for a crew
( nautical ) To do the proper work of a sailor
examples: The crewing of the vessel before the crash was deficient.

definitions.definition: ( nautical ) To take on, recruit (new) crew

main_definition: ( transitive and intransitive ) To be a member of a vessel's crew

definitions.definition: simple past of crow ( “ make the characteristic sound of a rooster ” ) .
examples: It was still dark when the cock crew .

main_definition: ( British , archaic ) simple past of crow ( “ make the characteristic sound of a rooster ” ) .
